# Frontend Standards

- Keep TypeScript strict; do not use `any`, non-null assertions, or unchecked casts.
- Default to React Server Components; add `'use client'` only at interactive boundaries.
- Keep route files thin and move focused UI into feature-local components.
- Use the generated API client; do not duplicate server DTOs or call undocumented endpoints.
- Treat URL search parameters as the source of truth for shareable filters and pagination.
- Prefer semantic HTML and native controls; preserve keyboard and screen-reader operation.
- Provide explicit loading, empty, error, and stale-data states.
- Do not use effects for derived state or routine data fetching.
- Avoid global client state until multiple routes demonstrably need shared mutable state.
- Keep components focused and tests behavior-oriented.
